data.text: Scarborough Company of Canada Scarborough's new map of the Dominion of Canada, showing provinces and territories, also Colony of Newfoundland : railways and steamship lines, principal cities, villages and stations, with distances between stations. Scale [ca. 1:3 500 000]. Hamilton, Ontario : Scarborough Company of Canada, c1916. 1 map : col. ; 93 x 147 cm. Includes index of places and table of distances. Insets: Scarborough's map of the world. Scale [ca. 1:217 000 000]. Newfoundland. Scale [ca. 1:3 500 000]. On verso: Western campaign, showing present location of trenches and farthest advance of the French and the Germans. Scale [ca. 1:2 400 000]. Italian campaign showing lines of opposing armies. Scale [ca. 1:1 900 000]. Scene of the western battles : detailed map of the region of main military operations along the Franco-Belgian-German frontiers. Scale [ca. 1:1 700 000]. Western theater of the war where Germany meets England, France and Belgium. Scale [ca. 1: 5 400 000]. Eastern campaign, showing the present location of battle front and farthest advance of Russians and Teutons. Scale [ca. 1: 5 400 000]. Southeastern Europe : Italy, Austria-Hungary, Balkan States and Turkey. Scale [ca. 1:4 900 000]. Asiatic campaigns, showing the field of British and Russian operations against Turkey. Scale [ca. 1:6 800 000]. British Isles. Scale [ca. 1:4 200 000]. Europe. Scale [ca. 1:19 500 000]. Austro-Italian boundary. Scale [ca. 1:1 400 000]. Constantinople and vicinity : Dardanelles, Sea of Marmora and Bosporus. Scale [ca. 1:1 200 000].
